metadata.name: Unicorn #1285
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

Twitter: @unicorn_nft_art
Web: https://unicorn-nft.web.app/

by @lucky26puch, @AgataBaranova17

metadata.name: a fleeting moment #143
metadata.description:
Abstract expressionism always has been, and always will be, my first love. With this piece, the initial premise was "can I write a bit of code that will render images in the style that I actually paint in real life?" 

It took several full days of poking and prodding, and I departed from the original mission once I had what I was looking for, but in general, I think I succeeded. My wife was looking over my shoulder at one point, and thought I was looking at a scan of one of my actual paintings, which sounds like success to me. 

Created with love in p5.js

metadata.name: Morning Mist #89
Tumble Down Light Factory #136
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden â€œtemplateâ€ canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden â€˜templateâ€™ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Summerland #80
metadata.description:
A random summer mountain landscape based on the technical core of 'Winterland'.
Varies in wind-strength, skycolor, depth and more.
Day/Night cycle based on your local system-time. 
Click/Tap for day/night change.

In Live-Mode...
...press 'r' to toggle responsive/fullscreen mode
...press 's' to save current frame
...click/tap/press space for day/night change

-@TeNinEightNFTs

Created with p5.js using map2.
